<br>
But I've found that resists are much more important for the actual fights. Just resisting the AoE twice, for instance, saves you more HPs than most of your slots filled with HP gear. (Well at least it does for me, heh).<br>
<br>
I'd go with a full suit of resist gear at first and then as you level and upgrade (getting gear with the HPs AND the resists on it, as ToV tends to do for people), switch out as you go.<br>
<br>
I do know my guild's MT worries about the same thing, sacrificing HPs for resists when he has to stand there and get wailed on by these mobs.<br>
<br>
But the resists just save you so much more during these fights, I've learned.<br>
<br>
Also, you can seek out gear that already does both jobs that is tradable. Like, Bracelet of Fortitude for instance, doesn't scrimp on the HPs with 15 STA ... has ok AC with 12 ... and has 6 to all saves. That's not really losing much if you switch out, say, a Silver Chitin Wristband for it.<br>
<br>
-Wubao<br>
